evoter.server.http

Class URIUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • evoter.server.http.URIUtils

  • public class URIUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is an request utility that checks request type based on URI string,
    fix encoding character of request parameters and write response to client via HttpExchange
    Author:
    btdiem

      • getParameters

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getParameters(com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpExchange exchange)
        Read and parse the string value from the request body into pairs value and put them to Map.
        If client put a list or an array to request body like String[] colors = { "blue", "yellow" }
        , server will receive an url parameter like : "colors[]=blue;colors[]=yellow"
        this method will convert these to an array. Finally, the method will returns a map that
        key is colors, value is String[]{"blue","yellow"} as example above
        Parameters:
        exchange - HttpExchange communicates between clients and server
        Returns:
        Map that contains parameter key and parameter values
